    "paragraphs": [
      {
        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Using the **matched 25 °C, I = 0.1 M** data from SRD-46:\n\n| Quantity | Value |\n|---|---:|\n| pKa1 of malonic acid | 2.65 |\n| pKa2 of malonic acid | 5.27 |\n| log K for Cu²⁺ + L²⁻ ⇌ CuL | 5.04 |\n\nHere **L²⁻ = malonate**. At **pH 4**, only a fraction of total malonate is present as \\(L^{2-}\\), so the **conditional** constant is\n\n\\[\nK' = K\\,\\alpha_{L^{2-}}\n\\]\n\nFor diprotic malonic acid,\n\n\\[\n\\alpha_{L^{2-}}=\n\\frac{K_{a1}K_{a2}}{[H^+]^2+[H^+]K_{a1}+K_{a1}K_{a2}}\n\\]\n\nwith\n\n\\[\nK_{a1}=10^{-2.65},\\quad K_{a2}=10^{-5.27},\\quad [H^+]=10^{-4}\n\\]\n\nNumerically:\n\n| Term | Value |\n|---|---:|\n| \\(K_{a1}\\) | \\(2.24\\times 10^{-3}\\) |\n| \\(K_{a2}\\) | \\(5.37\\times 10^{-6}\\) |\n| \\(K_{a1}K_{a2}\\) | \\(1.20\\times 10^{-8}\\) |\n| \\([H^+]^2\\) | \\(1.00\\times 10^{-8}\\) |\n| \\([H^+]K_{a1}\\) | \\(2.24\\times 10^{-7}\\) |\n| Denominator | \\(2.46\\times 10^{-7}\\) |\n| \\(\\alpha_{L^{2-}}\\) | \\(4.90\\times 10^{-2}\\) |\n\nSo only about **4.9%** of total malonate is in the binding form \\(L^{2-}\\) at pH 4.\n\nNow:\n\n\\[\nK' = 10^{5.04}\\times 0.0490\n\\]\n\nor in log form,\n\n\\[\n\\log K' = 5.04 + \\log(0.0490) = 5.04 - 1.31 \\approx 3.73\n\\]",
